'''Rainbow Rocks''' is the title [[Songs|song]] from ''[[My Little Pony Equestria Girls: Rainbow Rocks]]''. It serves as the first song in the film, playing during the film's opening [[credits]]. The intro snippet is heard during the teaser trailer from [[Wikipedia: San Diego Comic Con International|San Diego Comic Con 2014]], and a snippet of the song can also be heard in the trailer released by Shout! Factory as well as at the end of every sneak peek of the film released by Hasbro on YouTube. The song serves as the first track on the [[My Little Pony Equestria Girls: Rainbow Rocks - Original Motion Picture Soundtrack]]. On the soundtrack album, Twilight's solo is accompanied by harmony vocals, which are not heard in the film.

The song also appears at the end of the [[Chapter books|chapter book]] ''[[Twilight's Sparkly Sleepover Surprise]]'' by Perdita Finn.

